# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# TeleBotHost MCP Server — Environment Variables
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# This file is for LOCAL development only. For MCP client setup (Claude Desktop,
# Cursor, VS Code), set the env var in your client's MCP config — not here.
#
# See README.md → "Quick Start" for client-specific instructions.

# REQUIRED: Your TeleBotHost Developer API key.
# Get it from: https://telebothost.com → Developer Settings → API Keys
#   sk_*  = secret key (full write access) — keep private
#   pub_* = public key (read-only) — safe for client-side
TELEBOTHOST_API_KEY=sk_your_secret_key_here

# OPTIONAL: Override the API base URL (defaults to https://api.telebothost.com/api/v1)
# TELEBOTHOST_API_BASE=https://api.telebothost.com/api/v1

# OPTIONAL: Only for HTTP server mode (server.ts / self-hosting).
# Protects the HTTP MCP endpoint with a shared secret. Ignored in stdio mode.
# MCP_AUTH_TOKEN=your-mcp-access-token

# OPTIONAL: Port for HTTP server mode (server.ts). Auto-set by Render/Railway.
# PORT=3000
